cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about multiple face analysis tasks, such as landmark detection, head pose estimation, gender recognition, and face attribute estimation, which are all related to computer vision. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel deep multi-task adversarial learning method, which involves training a deep recognition network and a discriminator, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing facial images, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper uses adversarial learning, which is a technique commonly used in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
